<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[297,1693,1343,2157]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
A medium-sized, uniformly reddish yellow species, near 
<taxonomicName authority="Motschulsky" authorityName="Motschulsky" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scopaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testaceus">
<emphasis box="[1366,1693,2014,2054]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Scopaeus testaceus</emphasis>
Motschulsky
</taxonomicName>
, easily separated from it however, by the much wider and shorter, posteriorly broader head.
</paragraph>
